;(First interaction)
:----
:;(Screen fades to black)
::*ding* *ding* *ding* This tall blacksmith is forging iron.
::In your eyes, his weapon forging process is unsophisticated, unpretentious. Apart from exhibiting more strength and producing louder clanging, he doesn't seem too different from the most ordinary blacksmiths in Amphoreus.
::But... *ding* *ding* *ding*
::You notice a few pieces of quenched iron billets in his hands, glowing with an apparently unusual sheen.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Try interrupting him.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034006-->
::;(Screen fades to black)
:::'''Chartonus:''' ...
:::*ding* *ding* *ding* ...Nope, the blacksmith ignores you completely.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504034009-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Wait for him to finish.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034009-->
:;(Screen fades to black)
::Good thing this burly smith is almost done. The billet sizzles when doused in water, and Chartonus finally turns around to meet you.
::'''Chartonus:''' ...Long have you waited, warrior of the outlands.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} It's all right. I was just admiring your craft.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You knew I was waiting for you!
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034013-->
::'''Chartonus:''' Sorry, distracted I cannot be, while the smithing goes on.
::'''Chartonus:''' The earnest Titan, Georios. Its creations, the mountain dwellers are. Meticulous... a lineage unbroken.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} That iron billet feels very special...
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034016-->
:::'''Chartonus:''' Billet, ordinary it was. The tempering process, blessed by Titans it was.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504034018-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What kind of Titan is Georios?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034018-->
::'''Chartonus:''' The Pillar of Stone, Georios, the Earth Titan, God of the Mountains.
::'''Chartonus:''' Steady and diligent, Georios likes. Forge, grain, and strength, all shall gain.
::'''Chartonus:''' Hammer strikes, shape not alone. Earth's blessing, grasp strength, within seal it is.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} So it's enchanted with magic!
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034022-->
:::'''Chartonus:''' Magic... what is it? Craft, or raw material, is it?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} No wonder Dan Heng's spear was cut in half.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034024-->
:::'''Chartonus:''' Very special, his weapon is, that Lord Dan Heng.
:::'''Chartonus:''' Craftsmanship like this, seen before, I have not. No Titan's blessing it has, yet sharp and strong it is.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You crafted all the Chrysos Heirs' weapons?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034027-->
:::'''Chartonus:''' The Chrysos Heirs, trust me, they do.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504034028-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034028-->
::'''Chartonus:''' ...
::'''Chartonus:''' Continue my work, I shall, if nothing else there is, warrior of the outlands.
