:{{DIcon}} I want to have a chat with you.
::'''Chartonus:''' Chat, I do not well. Worry, you should not.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_504034003_64-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_504034003_64-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} How do I choose a good weapon in Amphoreus?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034103-->
:::'''Chartonus:''' Sharp and strong, a good weapon is... Like a hard rock, the red earth is.
:::'''Chartonus:''' Majestic and cold, a better weapon is... Like a throne, the chariot is.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What's the difference?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034106-->
:::'''Chartonus:''' Forge weapons, Georios does. Temper weapons, Nikador shall.
:::'''Chartonus:''' Explain well, I cannot. "Have become used to it," said once Phainon.
:::'''Chartonus:''' "Drenched in too much blood," said too Mydei.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} How well do you know the Chrysos Heirs?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034110-->
:::'''Chartonus:''' Good weapons, I craft for Chrysos Heirs. From weapons, my knowledge begins.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_504034003_76-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_504034003_76-->
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Mydei?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034112-->
::::'''Chartonus:''' His weapon, many times, Mydei has broken. A hum, I hear, when fixing the surviving weapons.
::::'''Chartonus:''' Cross the battlefield, through seas of blood, one shall. Only then, silent war cries, find you will.
::::'''Chartonus:''' Mostly like that, Kremnoan weapons are. Different, Mydei's is.
::::'''Chartonus:''' Divinity, majesty, compassion, there are. Rusted blood, many strange scents, mixed they are.
::::'''Chartonus:''' ...Misperception, perhaps it is.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Phainon?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034118-->
::::'''Chartonus:''' Lacks soul, Phainon's weapon does. Understand, I do not, why for such a resolute warrior, it is so.
::::'''Chartonus:''' Perhaps the weapon, not fitting it is. Perhaps hesitation there is, with destiny.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Aglaea?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034121-->
::::'''Chartonus:''' Need, Aglaea does not. Like her style, sharp and merciless, gold thread is.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Tribbie?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034123-->
::::'''Chartonus:''' Weapons, little girls have not. But often, see them I do.
::::'''Chartonus:''' Sometimes like thunder, the sound of hammering is. Startled, they are, when nearby by chance.
::::'''Chartonus:''' Little toys, they cannot make. Seek my help, they occasionally do.
::::'''Chartonus:''' Small rocket launchers, metal wings, iron horses... Craft them, I can. Adorable, they are.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Return}} Got it, no more questions from me.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_504034003_64-->
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} How do I choose a good weapon in Amphoreus?
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034103-->
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Sharp and strong, a good weapon is... Like a hard rock, the red earth is.
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Majestic and cold, a better weapon is... Like a throne, the chariot is.
:::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What's the difference?
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034106-->
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Forge weapons, Georios does. Temper weapons, Nikador shall.
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Explain well, I cannot. "Have become used to it," said once Phainon.
:::::'''Chartonus:''' "Drenched in too much blood," said too Mydei.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} The Mountain Dwellers sure have a lot of stories.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034129-->
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Too long, too long, the stories of the Mountain Dweller are. Busy, my hands are. Time to tell, I have not. Apologies, I offer.
:::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Just for a bit!
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034131-->
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Long history, Mountain Dwellers have. Their bodies, Georios shaped.
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Strong, Earth Titan's children are. For fairness, wisdom, Cerces gives not.
:::::<!--1-second delay-->
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Slaves, Mountain Dwellers once were. Taken, they were, to be blacksmiths, guards, miners, and keepers.
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Now Mountain Dwellers in Okhema, my people are. Used by Kremnoans, they once were.
:::::<!--1-second delay-->
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Love peace, Mountain Dwellers do. Yet, safe from war, hiding in mountains is not.
:::::'''Chartonus:''' With other civilizations, we exchange. Fortunate or unfortunate, think deeply we do not. Willing to ponder, we are not.
:::::<!--1-second delay-->
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Slow, Mountain Dwellers run. Curled up, we did when leaving the mountains, like rolling stones.
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Fear us, common folk did. But kind, everyone was. Accepted, we slowly were. "Gentle giants," they called us.
:::::<!--1-second delay-->
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Think little, work plenty, Mountain Dwellers do. Renowned for years, our forging skills and masonry have been.
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Kingdoms, we have not. In cities, we live. Content with stability, we are.
:::::<!--1-second delay-->
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Ores and soil, Mountain Dwellers like. Explosives and cold water, Mountain Dwellers hate.
:::::'''Chartonus:''' The city of Phagousa's faith, we rarely visit. Okhema, our favorite, it is so far.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::::{{DIcon|Exit}} Let's leave it there for now.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504034144-->
:::::'''Chartonus:''' Farewell, warrior. Bless you, the earth does.
:::::<!--Ends the current performance-->
